content.description: Climb up the fridge like arete from a stand start.
content.protection: A few pads or more.  Landing is a bit weird.
content.location: Just Right of Fat Raccoon on the same block.  Parrallel the North shore beach walking towards the west bluff and go straight uphill from the bench at the trail intersection a couple hundred feet.

content.description: Start sitting underneath the roof on low holds and do a few cool but dabby moves to the jug at chest level and then climb into squirrel arete.  Pretty fun.  If you start at the jug it is about v5 and good.
content.protection: A few pads or more, the landing is not perfect
content.location: Just below el parasol project on the fat raccoon boulder

climbs.name: Fat Raccoon Sit aka Skinny Raccoon

content.description: StartÂ on the low holds at the bottom of the roof and climb Fat Raccoon. The full line.
content.location: About 200 feet up the hill on the west side of the North shore beach and a little bit north.

content.description: Starting right hand in the jug and left hand underneath the roof climb up and left encountering some tough moves along the way.  A low start is possible and will bump the difficulty up.
content.protection: A few pads.  The landing is not perfect. 4 would be good.
content.location: Just below el parasol project.  Or from the north shore beach where the trails intersect near the tumbled rocks trail head up hill a couple hundred feet above the bench.

content.description: A large, steep boulder with a prominent cut-out.
